trans-unit.source: Sync Service Manager
trans-unit.target: Sync Service Manager

trans-unit.source: The option **Delete connector space only** will remove all data, but keep all configuration.
trans-unit.target: The option **Delete connector space only** will remove all data, but keep all configuration.

trans-unit.source: The option **Delete Connector and connector space** will remove the data as well as all configuration.
trans-unit.target: The option **Delete Connector and connector space** will remove the data as well as all configuration.

trans-unit.source: This is used when you do not want to connect to a forest anymore.
trans-unit.target: This is used when you do not want to connect to a forest anymore.

trans-unit.source: Both options will sync all objects and update the metaverse objects.
trans-unit.target: Both options will sync all objects and update the metaverse objects.

trans-unit.source: This is a long running operation.

trans-unit.source: Start by selecting a **scope**.
trans-unit.target: Start by selecting a **scope**.

trans-unit.source: If you for example do a Sub-Tree search you get all objects in one OU.
trans-unit.target: If you for example do a Sub-Tree search you get all objects in one OU.

trans-unit.target: From this you can select an object, select **properties** and [follow it](#follow-an-object-and-its-data-through-the-system) from the source connector space, through the metaverse, and to the target connector space.

trans-unit.target: Follow an object and its data through the system

trans-unit.source: When you open a cs object, there are several tabs at the top.
trans-unit.target: When you open a cs object, there are several tabs at the top.

trans-unit.source: The **Import** tab shows the data which is staged after an import.
trans-unit.target: The **Import** tab shows the data which is staged after an import.

trans-unit.source: ![Sync Service Manager](./media/active-directory-aadconnectsync-service-manager-ui/csimport.png)
trans-unit.target: ![Sync Service Manager](./media/active-directory-aadconnectsync-service-manager-ui/csimport.png)

trans-unit.source: The **Old Value** shows what currently is stored in the system and the **New Value** what has been received from the source system and has not been applied yet.
trans-unit.target: The **Old Value** shows what currently is stored in the system and the **New Value** what has been received from the source system and has not been applied yet.

trans-unit.source: In this case since there is a synchronization error, the change cannot be applied.
trans-unit.target: In this case since there is a synchronization error, the change cannot be applied.

trans-unit.source: Error
trans-unit.target: Error

trans-unit.source: The error page is only visible if there is a problem with the object.
trans-unit.target: The error page is only visible if there is a problem with the object.

trans-unit.source: See the details on the operations page for more information on how to [troubleshoot synchronization errors](active-directory-aadconnectsync-service-manager-ui-operations.md#troubleshoot-errors-in-operations-tab).

trans-unit.source: Lineage
trans-unit.target: Lineage

trans-unit.source: The lineage tab shows how the connector space object is related to the metaverse object.
trans-unit.target: The lineage tab shows how the connector space object is related to the metaverse object.

trans-unit.source: We can see when we last imported a change from the connected system and which rules applied to populate data in the metaverse.
trans-unit.target: We can see when we last imported a change from the connected system and which rules applied to populate data in the metaverse.

trans-unit.source: ![Sync Service Manager](./media/active-directory-aadconnectsync-service-manager-ui/cslineage.png)
trans-unit.target: ![Sync Service Manager](./media/active-directory-aadconnectsync-service-manager-ui/cslineage.png)

trans-unit.source: In the **Action** column we can see there is one **Inbound** sync rule with the action **Provision**.
trans-unit.target: In the **Action** column we can see there is one **Inbound** sync rule with the action **Provision**.

trans-unit.source: That indicates that as long as this connector space object is present, the metaverse object will remain.
trans-unit.target: That indicates that as long as this connector space object is present, the metaverse object will remain.

trans-unit.source: If the list of sync rules instead shows a sync rule with direction **Outbound** and **Provision** it indicates that this object will be deleted when the metaverse object is deleted.
trans-unit.target: If the list of sync rules instead shows a sync rule with direction **Outbound** and **Provision** it indicates that this object will be deleted when the metaverse object is deleted.

trans-unit.source: ![Sync Service Manager](./media/active-directory-aadconnectsync-service-manager-ui/cslineageout.png)
trans-unit.target: ![Sync Service Manager](./media/active-directory-aadconnectsync-service-manager-ui/cslineageout.png)

trans-unit.source: We can also see in the **PasswordSync** column that the inbound connector space can contribute changes to the password since one sync rule has the value **True**.
trans-unit.target: We can also see in the **PasswordSync** column that the inbound connector space can contribute changes to the password since one sync rule has the value **True**.

trans-unit.source: This password is then sent to Azure AD through the outbound rule.
trans-unit.target: This password is then sent to Azure AD through the outbound rule.

trans-unit.source: From the lineage tab you can get to the metaverse by clicking on [Metaverse Object Properties](#metaverse-object-properties).
trans-unit.target: From the lineage tab you can get to the metaverse by clicking on [Metaverse Object Properties](#metaverse-object-properties).

trans-unit.source: At the bottom of all tabs are two buttons: **Preview** and **Log**.
trans-unit.target: At the bottom of all tabs are two buttons: **Preview** and **Log**.

trans-unit.source: Preview
trans-unit.target: Preview

trans-unit.source: The preview page is used to synchronize one single object.
trans-unit.target: The preview page is used to synchronize one single object.

trans-unit.source: It is useful if you are troubleshooting some customer sync rules and want to see the effect of a change on a single object.
trans-unit.target: It is useful if you are troubleshooting some customer sync rules and want to see the effect of a change on a single object.

trans-unit.source: You can select between **Full Sync** and **Delta sync**.
trans-unit.target: You can select between **Full Sync** and **Delta sync**.

trans-unit.source: You can also select between **Generate Preview**, which will only keep the change in memory, and **Commit Preview**, which will stage all changes to target connector spaces.
trans-unit.target: You can also select between **Generate Preview**, which will only keep the change in memory, and **Commit Preview**, which will stage all changes to target connector spaces.

trans-unit.source: ![Sync Service Manager](./media/active-directory-aadconnectsync-service-manager-ui/preview1.png)
trans-unit.target: ![Sync Service Manager](./media/active-directory-aadconnectsync-service-manager-ui/preview1.png)

trans-unit.source: You can inspect the object and which rule applied for a particular attribute flow.
trans-unit.target: You can inspect the object and which rule applied for a particular attribute flow.

trans-unit.source: ![Sync Service Manager](./media/active-directory-aadconnectsync-service-manager-ui/preview2.png)
trans-unit.target: ![Sync Service Manager](./media/active-directory-aadconnectsync-service-manager-ui/preview2.png)

trans-unit.source: Log
trans-unit.target: Log

trans-unit.source: The Log page is used to see the password sync status and history, see [Troubleshoot password synchronization](active-directory-aadconnectsync-implement-password-synchronization.md#troubleshoot-password-synchronization) for more information.
trans-unit.target: The Log page is used to see the password sync status and history, see [Troubleshoot password synchronization](active-directory-aadconnectsync-implement-password-synchronization.md#troubleshoot-password-synchronization) for more information.
